one of Lucky Luciano's
oldest friends

36:45.571 --> 36:48.972
and business partners,
has been murdered.

36:50.908 --> 36:53.510
And while the mob has moved
quickly to take over

36:53.512 --> 36:55.312
Siegel's hotel in Las Vegas

36:55.314 --> 36:57.881
and Luciano's authority
has been restored...

36:59.717 --> 37:02.419
another member of
Luciano's operation

37:02.421 --> 37:05.989
begins organizing
his own fight for control.

37:09.493 --> 37:12.662
Frustrated by his lack of
power within the Mafia...

37:14.265 --> 37:18.001
Vito Genovese
wants to be boss again

37:18.003 --> 37:22.239
and begins to look outside
the Luciano family for help.

37:25.343 --> 37:27.544
He reaches out
to a mid-level gangster

37:27.546 --> 37:29.613
in one of the other
New York families.

37:29.615 --> 37:32.382
A 46-year-old
Sicilian underboss

37:32.384 --> 37:34.784
in the Mangano family

37:34.786 --> 37:37.320
named
Carlo Gambino.

37:39.257 --> 37:41.258
Why don't you tell me
what's on your mind?

37:41.260 --> 37:44.027
(sighs)

37:47.265 --> 37:50.267
I don't know how much more of
this crap I can take, Carlo.

37:50.269 --> 37:52.302
Oh, you know Lucky.

37:52.304 --> 37:55.038
The man holds
a grudge.

37:56.540 --> 37:58.908
You think I plan on taking
orders from the Manganos

37:58.910 --> 38:01.544
and Anastasia
the rest of my life?

38:01.546 --> 38:04.848
So what are you waiting for?
The right opportunity.

38:04.850 --> 38:06.916
As should you.

38:08.719 --> 38:10.887
Just stay
in the game.

38:20.831 --> 38:23.633
(narrator)
Genovese sees an ally
in Gambino.

38:26.637 --> 38:28.838
A like-minded mobster
with ambitions

38:28.840 --> 38:31.374
of climbing the ranks
of the New York Mafia.

38:33.010 --> 38:35.745
Carlo Gambino was old school,

38:35.747 --> 38:38.381
quiet, reticent,

38:38.383 --> 38:41.951
secretive,
very secretive.

38:48.025 --> 38:49.926
(narrator)
While Genovese and Gambino

38:49.928 --> 38:52.962
wait for their chance
to make a move,

38:52.964 --> 38:56.900
a new challenge rises
for the New York underworld.

38:56.902 --> 38:59.703
In May of 1950,

38:59.705 --> 39:03.707
an ambitious U.S. senator
named Estes Kefauver

39:03.709 --> 39:07.610
forms a committee
to investigate the Mafia,

39:07.612 --> 39:09.779
including New York's
most notorious mobsters.

39:11.415 --> 39:14.417
It's the largest effort
to expose organized crime

39:14.419 --> 39:16.052
in U.S. history

39:16.054 --> 39:19.723
in what will come to be known
as the Kefauver Hearings.

39:19.725 --> 39:21.825
A Senate investigating
committee

39:21.827 --> 39:24.894
held a series of hearings
to get at organized crime.

39:24.896 --> 39:27.564
In addition, they made
the very smart decision

39:27.566 --> 39:29.899
to televise
some of the hearings.

39:29.901 --> 39:32.635
(narrator)
In front of a television
audience of 30 million,

39:32.637 --> 39:34.904
the Mafia takes the stand.

39:34.906 --> 39:37.674
I decline to answer
on the grounds

39:37.676 --> 39:39.442
that it may incriminate me.

39:39.444 --> 39:41.678
I refuse to answer

39:41.680 --> 39:45.081
on the grounds that it may
tend to incriminate me.

39:45.083 --> 39:47.016
(Goodman)
The witnesses are very cool.

39:47.018 --> 39:49.919
They just take the Fifth,
which the Constitution provides,

39:49.921 --> 39:52.722
and say they're not going to
tend to incriminate them.

39:57.561 --> 39:59.496
(narrator)
As the hearings drag on,

39:59.498 --> 40:01.531
acting boss Frank Costello

40:01.533 --> 40:04.434
begins to see his name
mentioned in the press,

40:04.436 --> 40:07.670
often linked to horrific
murders and crimes.

40:10.007 --> 40:12.675
When he's finally
called to testify,

40:12.677 --> 40:16.012
Costello decides to take
a different approach.

40:19.550 --> 40:22.619
Frank, you have to
listen to me.
I'm listening.

40:22.621 --> 40:25.622
You gotta take the Fifth.
That's what makes you
look guilty.

40:25.624 --> 40:28.024
Moses, will you
talk to him?

40:28.026 --> 40:30.960
Frank,
the more you talk,

40:30.962 --> 40:33.029
the more trouble
you're gonna get into.

40:33.031 --> 40:35.965
I can talk
to these men.

40:35.967 --> 40:38.568
(Talese)
Frank Costello
was rather unique.

40:38.570 --> 40:41.805
He had hope,
aspiration and drive

40:41.807 --> 40:44.174
to be perceived

40:44.176 --> 40:46.543
as a somewhat
legitimate person.

40:46.545 --> 40:49.078
And he thought he was part
of American capitalism.

40:50.881 --> 40:54.083
What have you ever done for
your country as a U.S. citizen?

40:57.221 --> 40:58.988
(clearing throat)
Paid my tax.

40:58.990 --> 41:02.592
(crowd murmuring)

41:02.594 --> 41:05.161
(Raab)
Frank Costello
went before TV cameras

41:05.163 --> 41:06.830
when there was
an investigation

41:06.832 --> 41:09.165
into organized crime
in America.

41:09.167 --> 41:10.867
He thought he could outwit

41:10.869 --> 41:14.003
some lowly
prosecutor or lawyer.

41:14.005 --> 41:17.474
Do you want to
qualify your answer?

41:17.476 --> 41:19.576
Yes, I'd like
to qualify it.

41:19.578 --> 41:21.778
How so?

41:21.780 --> 41:23.913
I want what I said,

41:23.915 --> 41:25.715
specifically
what I said,

41:25.717 --> 41:28.117
on the official record.

41:28.119 --> 41:30.186
(Green)
Costello made a mistake

41:30.188 --> 41:32.689
in thinking
that he could handle

41:32.691 --> 41:34.791
a Senate
investigating committee

41:34.793 --> 41:37.527
the way he handled
local politicians.

41:37.529 --> 41:39.863
They're different
breeds of cat.

41:39.865 --> 41:42.232
(Senator)
<i>It contradicts</i>

41:42.234 --> 41:45.635
<i>your earlier testimony.</i>

41:45.637 --> 41:48.204
(Costello)
<i>No, it doesn't.</i>

41:48.206 --> 41:50.273
(Senator)
<i>Would you like me</i>
<i>to refresh your memory?</i>

41:50.275 --> 41:52.976
(Costello)
<i>Ahem, you don't need</i>
<i>to refresh my memory.</i>

41:52.978 --> 41:54.777
<i>My memory's fine.</i>

41:54.779 --> 41:56.579
(Senator)
<i>I'd be happy to read back</i>

41:56.581 --> 41:58.648
<i>your earlier testimony.</i>

41:58.650 --> 42:01.050
(Costello)
<i>I can refresh</i>
<i>my own memory, thank you.</i>

42:01.052 --> 42:04.220
Guy lost his mind.

42:04.222 --> 42:06.256
(narrator)
With the hearings revealing

42:06.258 --> 42:09.225
a weakness in
Costello's leadership,

42:09.227 --> 42:12.061
Vito Genovese
knows his opportunity

42:12.063 --> 42:15.298
has finally come.

42:15.300 --> 42:18.101
And with Carlo Gambino
on his side,

42:18.103 --> 42:21.604
Genovese is ready
to strike back

42:21.606 --> 42:23.606
at Lucky Luciano

42:23.608 --> 42:26.676
by taking down
Frank Costello.

